{"type":"message","id":"7bfa0afa","parentId":"0e948ed7","timestamp":"2026-04-04T09:26:16.387Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing with the same error - memory-lancedb is failing to load because it can't find package.json in the dist directory. This is a bug in OpenClaw - the plugin is trying to load from the wrong path.\n\nThe error:```\nmemory-lancedb failed to load from /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/memory-lancedb/index.js: Error: ENOENT: no such file or directory, open '/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/package.json'\n```The plugin path is correct (`dist/extensions/memory-lancedb/index.js`), but it's looking for `dist/package.json` which doesn't exist. The correct path should be either:1. `dist/extensions/memory-lancedb/package.json` (the plugin's own package.json)2. Or the root `package.json` at `openclaw/package.json`This looks like a bug in the OpenClaw memory-lancedb plugin - it's incorrectly looking for `dist/package.json` instead of looking in the right place.\n\nOptions:\n1. Try to fix this by creating a symlink or copying the file\n2. Report this as a bug to OpenClaw\n3. Disable lancedb and stick with memory-core\n\nLet me try to see if I can work around this by creating a symlink.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**又失败了！** 跟之前一样的问题：\n\n```\nmemory-lancedb failed to load: ENOENT: no such file or directory, \nopen '/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/package.json'\n```\n\n这是 OpenClaw 的 bug — 插件路径配置错误。让我试试修复：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dc4caa414a7149048867b11a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ln -sf ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/package.json ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/package.json 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":